nly%20exception%20to%20this%20is%20France%2C%20which%20retains%20a%20substantial%20Jewish%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EImplicit%20in%20this%20observation%20was%20that%20many%20of%20those%20in%20Europe%20who%20supported%20a%20homeland%20for%20the%20Jews%20in%20what%20had%20been%20the%20UN%20Mandate%20of%20Palestine%20under%20British%20rule%20were%20no%20friends%20of%20the%20Jews.%20They%20just%20wanted%20them%20gone.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fthe-israel-palestine-war-is-a-stain-on-every-one-of-us%5C%22%3EThe%20Israel-Palestine%20War%20Is%20a%20Stain%20on%20Every%20One%20of%20Us%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBalfour%E2%80%99s%20Lines%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFew%20people%20exemplified%20this%20better%20than%20Arthur%20Balfour%2C%20who%20as%20the%20British%20foreign%20secretary%20in%201917%2C%20wrote%20the%20Balfour%20Declaration%20%E2%80%93%20a%20letter%20to%20Lord%20Rotschild%20to%20be%20transmitted%20to%20the%20Zionist%20Federation%20of%20Great%20Britain%20and%20Ireland%2C%20promising%20a%20homeland%20for%20Jews%20in%20Palestine.%20As%20the%20Israeli%20historian%20Tom%20Segev%20shows%20in%20his%20excellent%20history%20of%20the%20Mandate%20period%2C%3Cem%3E%20One%20Palestine%2C%20Complete%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Balfour%20did%20not%20do%20this%20with%20any%20great%20sympathy%20for%20Jews.%20Instead%2C%20for%20complicated%20reasons%20%E2%80%93%20akin%20to%20anti-semitic%20myths%20of%C2%A0world%20controlling%20Jewish%20manipulators%20%E2%80%93%20he%20believed%20that%20Jews%20exerted%20enormous%20control%20over%20both%20the%20Bolshevik%20movement%20and%20the%20leadership%20of%20the%20United%20States.%20In%20the%20context%20of%20World%20War%20I%2C%20he%20wanted%20them%20%E2%80%9Conside%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20British%20Empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Balfour%20Declaration%20was%20both%20an%20impossible%20promise%20and%20a%20poisoned%20chalice%20for%20the%20Zionist%20movement%2C%20at%20that%20a%20very%20small%20part%20of%20the%20larger%20Jewish%20community.%20While%20the%20declaration%20promised%20the%20foundation%20of%20a%20homeland%2C%20it%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20it%20could%20not%20be%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20civil%20and%20religious%20rights%20of%20non-Jewish%20communities.%20At%20that%20point%20in%20time%2C%20the%20Jewish%20community%20in%20Mandatory%20Palestine%20was%20a%20tiny%20minority%20in%20what%20are%20now%20the%20internationally%20recognised%20pre-1967%20borders%20of%20Israel.%20Migration%20into%20Palestine%20was%20slow%20before%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20genocidal%20Nazi%20regime%2C%20and%20even%20that%20resulted%20in%20pushback%20from%20the%20Arab%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Palestinians%20%E2%80%93%20living%20in%20the%20region%2C%20as%20well%20as%20creating%20hostility%20among%20the%20bordering%20Arab%20states%2C%20who%20saw%20no%20reason%20why%20a%20Jewish%20homeland%20needed%20to%20be%20created%20in%20Palestine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04130747%2FStroop_Report_-_Warsaw_Ghetto_Uprising_06c.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04130747%2FStroop_Report_-_Warsaw_Ghetto_Uprising_06c.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04130747%2FStroop_Report_-_Warsaw_Ghetto_Uprising_06c-300x208.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04130747%2FStroop_Report_-_Warsaw_Ghetto_Uprising_06c-1024x709.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683475%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22831%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Warsaw%20Ghetto%20uprising%20became%20significant%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20Jewish%20resistance%20against%20the%20Nazis.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHow%20was%20one%20to%20create%20a%20Jewish%20homeland%20if%20the%20Jews%20were%20a%20minority%20could%20be%20answered%20in%20another%20way%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20same%20way%20that%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Canada%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20New%20Zealand%20became%20European%20majority%20states.%20Ethnic%20cleansing%20by%20settler%20colonial%20movements%20against%20%E2%80%9Cnatives%E2%80%9D%20had%20been%20the%20norm%20for%20centuries%2C%20and%20anti-colonial%20movements%20were%20far%20from%20achieving%20prominence.%20Nonetheless%2C%20this%20poison%20in%20the%20cup%20was%20acknowledged%20by%20its%20glaring%20omission.%20The%20Zionist%20slogan%20of%20%E2%80%9Ca%20land%20with%20no%20people%20for%20a%20people%20with%20no%20land%E2%80%9D%20tried%20to%20%E2%80%93%20at%20least%20verbally%20%E2%80%93%20cleanse%20Mandatory%20Palestine%20of%20the%20(non-Jewish)%20people%20who%20were%20very%20much%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20war%20that%20followed%20the%20establishment%20of%20Israel%2C%20the%20ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20a%20large%20section%20of%20Palestinians%20became%20a%20subsidiary%20goal%2C%20making%20Jews%20the%20majority%20in%20the%20UN-recognised%20borders%20of%20the%20new%20state.%20For%20a%20Jewish%20community%20that%20had%20seen%20its%20near%20extinction%20in%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20a%20place%20of%20security%20for%20its%20people%20had%2C%20understandably%2C%20become%20the%20ultimate%20objective.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnti-semite%20bigots%20shifted%20the%20burden%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20not%20just%20people%20that%20were%20displaced%20in%20the%20migration%20from%20Europe%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ednref1%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-israels-supporters-in-the-west-are-no-friends-of-jews%23_edn1%5C%22%3E%5Bi%5D%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20what%20would%20become%20Israel%2C%20guilt%20was%20shifted%20too.%20The%20murderous%20bigotry%20of%20anti-semitism%20was%20now%20considered%20the%20burden%20of%20Arabs%20who%20refused%20to%20accept%20a%20Jewish%20state%2C%20even%20by%20Palestinians%20whose%20family%20members%20had%20been%20murdered%2C%20brutalised%2C%20and%20ethnically%20cleansed%20from%20their%20lands.%20Those%20that%20had%20practiced%20centuries%20of%20Jew-hatred%20now%20portrayed%20themselves%20as%20%E2%80%9Cenlightened%E2%80%9D%20and%20lectured%20the%20world%20about%20anti-semitism.%20To%20be%20fair%2C%20there%20is%20enough%20anti-semitism%20to%20go%20around.%20Many%20of%20those%20speaking%20about%20the%20injustice%20meted%20out%20to%20the%20Palestinians%20did%20not%20distinguish%20between%20Israeli%20policies%20and%20Jewish%20people%2C%20and%20have%20bred%20a%20Jew-hatred%20of%20their%20own%2C%20as%20murderous%20as%20the%20one%20that%20once%20led%20to%20pogroms%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20bigots%2C%20though%2C%20this%20was%20wonderful.%20They%20could%20enjoy%20the%20sight%20of%20one%20people%20they%20despised%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Jews%20%E2%80%93%20fighting%20with%20another%20set%20of%20people%20they%20despised%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnatives%E2%80%9D.%20Large%20parts%20of%20the%20European%20world%20have%20never%20confronted%2C%20or%20given%20up%2C%20either%20their%20anti-semitism%2C%20or%20their%20colonial%20attitudes%2C%20and%20this%20came%20with%20an%20added%20bonus%20%E2%80%93%20if%20Jews%20were%20committing%20crimes%20against%20humanity%2C%20then%20this%20could%20be%20used%20to%20(illegitimately)%20normalise%20past%20crimes%20against%20the%20Jewish%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fby-fully-supporting-israel-the-west-has-chosen-to-forget-the-suffering-of-palestinians%5C%22%3EBy%20Fully%20Supporting%20Israel%2C%20the%20West%20Has%20Chosen%20to%20Forget%20the%20Suffering%20of%20Palestinians%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETricky%20questions%20ahead%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20this%20history%20is%20important%20is%20that%20%E2%80%93%20at%20a%20time%20of%20war%20between%20Israelis%20and%20Palestinians%20that%20exceeds%20every%20round%20of%20violence%20except%20for%20the%20foundation%20of%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20all%20these%20contradictions%20are%20increasingly%20clear.%20The%20Israelis%20were%20given%20a%20poisoned%20gift%2C%20one%20that%20gave%20them%20a%20state%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20another%20people%E2%80%99s%20dignity.%20Some%20of%20them%2C%20those%20on%20the%20extremist%20right%2C%20have%20always%20embraced%20this%2C%20and%20even%20now%20speak%20of%20annihilating%20or%20ethnically%20cleansing%20the%20Palestinians%20that%20remain.%20A%20large%20set%2C%20though%2C%20has%20always%20struggled%20to%20reconcile%20these%20issues%2C%20knowing%20that%20their%20tragedy%20was%20one%20of%20two%20demands%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Jewish%20need%20for%20safety%20and%20the%20Palestinian%20need%20for%20human%20dignity%20%E2%80%93%20that%20were%20set%20against%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20such%20a%20time%2C%20the%20non-extremist%20Israelis%20need%20their%20friends%2C%20those%20who%20would%20try%20to%20help%20them%20find%20a%20just%20solution%20that%20can%20somehow%20answer%20this%20impossible%20question.%20Unfortunately%2C%20they%20are%20confronted%20with%20a%20world%20in%20which%20their%20most%20vociferous%20supporters%20are%20those%20that%20are%20themselves%20difficult%20to%20trust%2C%20who%20may%20even%20support%20war%20crimes%20because%20this%20delegitimises%20the%20horrors%20that%20Jews%20have%20faced.%20Ideally%2C%20they%20would%20have%20found%20partners%20among%20post-colonial%20countries%20who%20also%20have%20had%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20tragedies%20that%20European%20colonial%20left%20behind.%20India%2C%20of%20course%2C%20would%20have%20qualified.%20Sadly%2C%20though%2C%20it%20is%20now%20governed%20by%20exactly%20the%20same%20type%20of%20anti-semites%20and%20bigots%20that%20cheer%20on%20Israeli%20extremists%20in%20this%20unwinnable%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_edn1%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-israels-supporters-in-the-west-are-no-friends-of-jews%23_ednref1%5C%22%3E%5Bi%5D%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20story%20of%20the%20migration%20of%20Arab%20Jews%20is%20a%20separate%20story%20with%20its%20own%20betrayals%2C%20heartbreak%2C%20and%20racism.%20The%20Jews%20of%20Arab%20countries%20and%20North%20Africa%20are%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20Mizrahi%2C%20or%20%E2%80%9COriental%20Jews%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20number%20about%20half%20of%20the%20population%20of%20Israel%2C%20although%20very%20few%20of%20them%20have%20achieved%20political%20power%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20the%20former%20Defence%20Minister%2C%20Binyamin%20Ben-Eliezer%2C%20who%20often%20referred%20himself%20by%20the%20Arabic%20name%20Fuad.%20They%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fthe-roots-of-anti-mizrahi-racism-in-israel%2F%5C%22%3Etreated%20shockingly%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20newly%20established%20Israeli%20state%20dominated%20by%20European-origin%20Jews.%20The%20term%20Israeli%20Arab%20does%20not%20recognise%20Arab%20Jews%20and%20is%20an%20obvious%20way%20to%20avoid%20the%20racism%20inherent%20in%20referring%20to%20non-Jewish%20Arabs.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fomair-ahmad%5C%22%3EOmair%20Ahmad%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20author%20and%20journalist.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699084830000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F04130311%2FThe-Wire-68.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-israels-supporters-in-the-west-are-no-friends-of-jews%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Israelis%20were%20given%20a%20poisoned%20gift%2C%20one%20that%20gave%20them%20a%20state%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20another%20people%E2%80%99s%20dignity.%20Those%20on%20th