e%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20who%20proudly%20says%20during%20his%20visits%20abroad%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EMain%20Gandhi%20ke%20desh%20se%20hoon%3C%2Fem%3E%20(I%E2%80%99m%20from%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20country)%2C%E2%80%9D%20should%20revisit%20the%20Mahatma%E2%80%99s%20apprehensions%2C%20which%20he%20expressed%20on%20September%2017%2C%201931%2C%20that%20political%20parties%20would%20run%20the%20risk%20of%20using%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20only%20on%20managing%20elections.%20He%20described%20as%20atrocious%20a%20candidate%20spending%20Rs%2060%2C000-1%2C00%2C000%20in%20a%20poor%20country%20like%20India.%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20sharp%20observations%20on%20election%20expenditure%20were%20made%20in%20his%20speech%20delivered%20in%20the%20Federal%20Structure%20Committee%20of%20the%20second%20Round%20Table%20Conference%20held%20in%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThose%20apprehensions%20assume%20momentous%20significance%20when%20the%20BJP%20has%20got%20slightly%20more%20than%20Rs%2052%2C000%20crore%20from%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20introduced%20by%20the%20Modi%20regime%20in%202017%2C%20while%20opposition%20parties%20like%20Congress%20got%20only%20Rs%20952%20crore.%20Ninety-two%20years%20after%20he%20made%20those%20observations%2C%20India%20is%20witnessing%20the%20staggering%20amount%20of%20money%20collected%20by%20the%20BJP%20during%20the%20Modi%20regime%20and%20the%20huge%20quantum%20it%20spends%20for%2C%20in%20the%20words%20of%20Gandhi%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmanaging%20elections%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20prime%20minister%20also%20extols%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20and%20has%20never%20uttered%20a%20word%20against%20him%20in%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20he%20criticises%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20Indira%20Gandhi.%20He%20should%20also%20seriously%20revisit%20the%20report%20of%20the%20Santhanam%20Committee%20established%20by%20Shastri%20in%201962%2C%20during%20his%20tenure%20as%20home%20minister%2C%20to%20look%20into%20the%20magnitude%20of%20corruption%20in%20India%20and%20recommend%20measures%20to%20prevent%20it.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20committee%20in%20independent%20India%20set%20up%20to%20examine%20the%20gathering%20crisis%20of%20corruption%20and%20suggest%20remedial%20measures.%20The%20prescient%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Committee%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6all%20political%20parties%20should%20keep%20a%20proper%20account%20of%20their%20receipts%20and%20expenditure%20and%20publish%20annually%20an%20audited%20statement%20of%20such%20accounts%20giving%20details%20of%20all%20individual%20receipts%E2%80%9D%2C%20is%20of%20monumental%20significance%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20adjudication%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20attorney%20general%20for%20India%20has%20taken%20the%20bizarre%20stand%20that%20citizens%20do%20not%20have%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20know%20the%20source%20and%20volume%20of%20funds%20received%20by%20political%20parties.%20The%20Santhanam%20Committee%20made%20the%20far-reaching%20recommendation%20that%20there%20should%20be%20a%20law%20mandating%20political%20parties%20to%20disclose%20the%20details%20of%20funds%20received.%20It%20observed%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20see%20why%20any%20political%20party%20should%20object%20to%20this%20provision%2C%20and%20as%20it%20may%20not%20be%20easy%20to%20ensure%20compliance%20through%20voluntary%20agreement%2C%20simple%20legislation%20obliging%20the%20keeping%20of%20such%20accounts%20and%20its%20publication%20may%20be%20necessary.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Santhanam%20Committee%20upheld%20in%20the%20early%201960s%20that%20there%20should%20be%20legislation%20requiring%20political%20parties%20to%20put%20an%20account%20of%20money%20received%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20the%20Modi%20regime%20defends%20an%20opaque%20electoral%20bonds%20system%20through%20the%20instrumentality%20of%20law%2C%20and%20denies%20the%20right%20of%20people%20to%20know%20about%20those%20funds%2C%20which%20political%20parties%20use%20for%20participating%20in%20elections%20to%20get%20access%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worthwhile%20to%20dive%20a%20little%20deeper%20into%20the%20Santhanam%20Committee%20report%20and%20look%20at%20its%20farsighted%20observations%20on%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20corruption.%20It%20pointed%20out%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20public%20belief%20in%20the%20prevalence%20of%20corruption%20at%20high%20political%20levels%20has%20been%20strengthened%20by%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20funds%20are%20collected%20by%20political%20parties%2C%20especially%20at%20the%20time%20of%20elections.%E2%80%9D%20Acknowledging%20frankly%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpolitical%20parties%20cannot%20be%20run%20and%20elections%20cannot%20be%20fought%20without%20large%20funds%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20unequivocally%20asserted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthese%20funds%20should%20come%20openly%20from%20the%20supporters%20or%20sympathisers%20of%20the%20parties%20concerned.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Santhanam%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20stress%20on%20the%20point%20that%20accounts%20of%20political%20parties%20giving%20details%20of%20all%20individual%20receipts%20of%20funds%20should%20be%20published%20for%20the%20information%20of%20the%20people%20of%20India%2C%20and%20that%20such%20funds%20should%20be%20transferred%20openly%2C%20need%20to%20be%20flagged%20by%20the%20lawyers%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20arguing%20in%20favour%20of%20transparent%20process%20through%20which%20political%20parties%20should%20get%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20instructive%20to%20note%20that%20the%20Santhanam%20Committee%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20took%20the%20stand%20that%20corporations%20should%20be%20barred%20from%20funding%20political%20parties%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20consider%20that%20in%20Indian%20conditions%2C%20companies%20should%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20participate%20in%20politics%20through%20their%20donations.%E2%80%9D%20It%20observed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cafter%20the%20matter%20was%20debated%20at%20length%20during%20the%20discussion%20on%20the%20Companies%20(Amendment)%20Act%20of%201960%2C%20it%20was%20decided%20to%20permit%20such%20donations%20subject%20to%20restrictions%20of%20amount%20and%20condition%20of%20publication.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20it%20strongly%20opined%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20think%20that%20this%20is%20sufficient%20and%20feel%20that%20nothing%20but%20a%20total%20ban%20on%20all%20donations%20by%20incorporated%20bodies%20to%20political%20l%20parties%20and%20purposes%20will%20clear%20the%20atmosphere.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20educative%20to%20note%20that%20the%20Santhanam%20Committee%20suggested%20public%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%2C%20rather%20than%20corporate%20funding.%20It%20felt%20that%20if%20people%20would%20fund%20political%20parties%2C%20corruption%20related%20to%20election%20expenditure%20would%20be%20eradicated.%20It%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20even%20one%20family%20in%20three%20pays%20one%20rupee%20a%20year%20to%20a%20political%20party%2C%20the%20total%20annual%20contribution%20will%20be%20more%20than%20what%20is%20needed%20for%20all%20legitimate%20purposes%20of%20all%20political%20parties%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20A%20novel%20idea%2C%20indeed.%20It%20then%20referred%20to%20the%20reluctance%20and%20inability%20of%20the%20parties%20to%20make%20small%20collections%20on%20a%20wide%20basis%20and%20described%20their%20desire%20to%20resort%20to%20shortcuts%20through%20large%20donations%20as%20the%20major%20source%20of%20corruption%2C%20and%20even%20the%20suspicion%20of%20corruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20very%20profound%20observations%2C%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20massive%20funds%20the%20BJP%20got%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20corresponding%20increase%20in%20corruption%20in%20India%20on%20account%20of%20that%20opaque%20funding.%20The%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20el