a%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2023%2F05%2F1136662%5C%22%3Eapproximately%20700%2C000%20Palestinians%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0during%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fhl%3Den%26lr%3D%26id%3Doi8cmbTa6qMC%26oi%3Dfnd%26pg%3DPR7%26dq%3Dpalestine%2Bwar%2Bhistory%26ots%3DpCKeM1Nzzj%26sig%3D2lbV5e979b4VYA_-NqOhcfNXdPQ%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Dpalestine%2520war%2520history%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3EArab-Israeli%20War%20of%201948%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Funispal%2Fdocument%2Fauto-insert-189917%2F%5C%22%3Ecreation%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20of%20Palestine%E2%80%99s%20Arab%20population%20fled%20their%20homes%20during%20the%20war%2C%20seeking%20temporary%20refuge%20across%20the%20Middle%20East%20but%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.euppublishing.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.3366%2FE147494750800019X%5C%22%3Ehoping%20to%20return%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0after%20hostilities%20ceased.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20mass%20exodus%20of%20Palestinians%20in%201948%20resulted%20in%20two%20realities%20that%20have%20marked%20the%20region%20since.%20The%20first%20involved%20about%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcris.huji.ac.il%2Fen%2Fpublications%2Fthe-state-of-israel-versus-the-palestinian-internal-refugees%5C%22%3E25%2C000%20Palestinians%20displaced%20within%20the%20boundaries%20of%20what%20became%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Known%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmada-research.org%2Fstorage%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2Fenglish.indd_.pdf%23page%3D26%5C%22%3Einternally%20displaced%20Palestinians%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20community%20did%20not%20cross%20any%20official%20border%20and%20thus%20never%20received%20refugee%20status%20under%20international%20law.%20Instead%2C%20they%20became%20Israeli%20citizens%2C%20distinguished%20by%20their%20legal%20designation%20in%20Israel%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.palestine-studies.org%2Fen%2Fnode%2F1648031%5C%22%3Epresent%20absentees%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThrough%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jerusalemstory.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2Fhow-israel-applies-absentees-property-law-confiscate-palestinian-property-jerusalem%5C%22%3EAbsentee%20Property%20Law%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20Israeli%20state%20proceeded%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeasteye.net%2Fnews%2Fisrael-palestinian-absentees-property-law-eviction-homes-explained%5C%22%3Eto%20confiscate%20displaced%20Palestinians%E2%80%99%20properties%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fresearch%2F2022%2F02%2Fqa-israels-apartheid-against-palestinians-cruel-system-of-domination-and-crime-against-humanity%2F%5C%22%3Edeny%20their%20right%20to%20return%20to%20the%20homes%20and%20villages%20of%20their%20birth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20event%20involved%20over%20700%2C000%20Palestinians%20who%20fled%20beyond%20what%20became%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-54116567%5C%22%3Ede%20facto%20borders%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fwho-we-are%5C%22%3Eacquired%20formal%20refugee%20status%20under%20the%20United%20Nations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20group%20of%20refugees%20sought%20shelter%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ochaopt.org%2Fatlas2019%2F%5C%22%3Eareas%20of%20Palestine%20unconquered%20by%20Jewish%20forces%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20Nablus%20and%20Jenin%2C%20and%20in%20neighboring%20states%2C%20including%20Jordan%2C%20Syria%2C%20Lebanon%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fmreview.org%2Fsustainable-livelihoods%2Felabed%5C%22%3Eand%20Egypt%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EImmediately%20following%20their%20displacement%2C%20these%20Palestinians%20were%20subject%20to%20ad%20hoc%20support%20from%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.quakersintheworld.org%2Fquakers-in-action%2F216%5C%22%3Evarious%20international%20organizations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0until%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fcontent%2Fgeneral-assembly-resolution-302%5C%22%3Ethe%201949%20creation%20of%20the%20UNRWA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20assumed%20official%20responsibility%20for%20the%20management%20of%20direct%20relief%20operations%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fwhere-we-work%5C%22%3Erefugee%20camp%20infrastructure%20throughout%20the%20Middle%20East%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20providing%20education%2C%20health%20care%20and%20other%20services%2C%20including%20microfinancing%20and%20jobs%20training%2C%20the%20UNRWA%20has%20been%20supporting%20refugee%20camp%20improvement%20projects%20through%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fwhat-we-do%2Fimproving-conditions%3Fprogram%3D42%5C%22%3Eroad%20construction%20and%20home%20rehabilitation%20in%20the%20camps%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERefugees%20in%20Jordan%2C%20Egypt%20and%20Syria%3A%20the%20Naksa%20of%201967%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second-largest%20displacement%20of%20Palestinians%20occurred%20in%201967%20during%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Ffeatures%2F2018%2F6%2F4%2Fthe-naksa-how-israel-occupied-the-whole-of-palestine-in-1967%5C%22%3Ethe%20Israel-Arab%20war%20known%20to%20Palestinians%20as%20Al%20Naksa%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0or%20the%20%E2%80%9Csetback.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFought%20between%20Israel%20on%20one%20side%20and%20Syria%2C%20Egypt%20and%20Jordan%20on%20the%20other%2C%20the%20war%20ended%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fbooks%2Fedition%2F1967%2FwDhYMiAnidAC%3Fhl%3Den%26gbpv%3D1%26dq%3D1967%2Bwar%2Bisrael%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%5C%22%3EIsrael%20occupying%20territory%20in%20all%20three%20countries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20the%20remaining%20areas%20of%20Palestine%3A%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20Strip.%20During%20the%20war%2C%20approximately%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fwhere-we-work%2Fjordan%5C%22%3E400%2C000%20Palestinians%20were%20displaced%20from%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20primarily%20to%20Jordan%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20housed%20in%20one%20of%20six%20new%20UNRWA%20refugee%20camps.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOthers%20found%20refuge%20in%20Egypt%20and%20Syria.%20More%20than%20a%20third%20of%20those%20Palestinians%20displaced%20in%201967%20were%20already%20refugees%20from%201948%20and%20thus%20suffered%20a%20second%20forced%20migration.%20Just%20as%20in%201948%2C%20when%20the%201967%20war%20ended%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonline.ucpress.edu%2Fjps%2Farticle-abstract%2F36%2F3%2F6%2F53874%2FThe-June-1967-War-and-the-Palestinian-Refugee%5C%22%3EIsraeli%20government%20blocked%20the%20return%20of%20any%20refugees%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20proceeded%20to%20destroy%20several%20Palestinian%20villages%20in%20the%20occupied%20territory%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.taylorfrancis.com%2Fbooks%2Fmono%2F10.4324%2F9780203061428%2Fisrael-west-bank-international-law-allan-gerson%5C%22%3Eincluding%20Emmaus%2C%20Yula%20and%20Beit%20Yuba%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20their%20destruction%2C%20these%20areas%20were%20leased%20to%20Jewish%20Israelis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeyond%20Al-Nakba%20and%20Al-Naksa%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20tragedies%20of%20the%20Nakba%20and%20the%20Naksa%20turned%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20Palestinians%20into%20refugees%2C%20numerous%20events%20since%20then%20have%20increased%20their%20number.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20causes%20of%20Palestinian%20displacement%20today%20is%20the%20Israeli%20practice%20of%20home%20demolitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhether%20as%20a%20punitive%20measure%20or%20the%20result%20of%20a%20permit%20system%20that%20rights%20groups%20say%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fcampaigns%2F2022%2F02%2Fisraels-system-of-apartheid%2F%5C%22%3Esystematically%20discriminates%20against%20Palestinians%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20between%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ochaopt.org%2Fdata%2Fdemolition%5C%22%3E2009%20and%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20practice%20destroyed%20over%209%2C000%20homes%20and%20left%20approximately%2014%2C000%20Palestinians%20homeless.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20further%20displacement%20of%20Palestinians%20has%20also%20resulted%20from%20regional%20wars%20involving%20neither%20Palestinians%20nor%20Israelis.%20Following%20the%20end%20of%20Iraq%E2%80%99s%20occupation%20of%20Kuwait%20in%201990%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.badil.org%2Fpublications%2Fal-majdal%2Fissues%2Fitems%2F1355.html%5C%22%3Eover%20300%2C000%20Palestinians%20were%20expelled%20from%20Kuwait%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0retaliation%20for%20support%20offered%20by%20the%20leading%20Palestinian%20national%20organization%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fpalestineun.org%2Fabout-palestine%2Fpalestine-liberation-organization%2F%5C%22%3EPalestine%20Liberation%20Organization%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20Saddam%20Hussein.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Syrian%20Civil%20War%20in%202011%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fwhere-we-work%2Fsyria%5C%22%3Eover%20120%2C000%20Palestinian%20refugees%20have%20fled%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20primarily%20to%20Turkey%20and%20Jordan%2C%20while%20another%20200%2C000%20have%20been%20internally%20displaced.%20More%20recently%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2Fprojects%2Fisrael-hamas-war%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20already%20internally%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2023%2F10%2F1142687%5C%22%3Edisplaced%20over%201.4%20million%20Palestinians%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMany%20refugees%2C%20many%20exiles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBecause%20Palestinians%20live%20under%20various%20governments%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.2307%2F2538257%5C%22%3Ediverse%20circumstances%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20no%20single%20experience%20can%20account%20for%20their%20experience%20of%20exile.%20In%20Jordan%2C%20for%20example%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F13642987.2010.482911%5C%22%3Ewhere%20I%20have%20conducted%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Palestinian%20refugees%20can%20be%20divided%20into%20numerous%20groups%2C%20each%20with%20its%20own%20set%20of%20opportunities%20and%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20Palestinians%20displaced%20in%201948%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.alawdaeu.prc.org.uk%2Findex.php%2Fen%2Fpalestine%2Frefugees%2F582-%5C%22%3Ewho%20became%20citizens%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20Jordan%20but%20depend%20on%20UNRWA%20for%20basic%20services%20like%20education%20and%20health%20care.%20There%20are%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcommons.memphis.edu%2Ffacpubs%2F169%2F%5C%22%3Erefugees%20displaced%20from%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20in%201967%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0who%20lack%20citizenship%20and%20are%20thus%20deprived%20of%20certain%20civil%20and%20political%20rights.%20More%20recently%2C%20there%20are%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fcampaigns%2F2013%2F07%2Fa-dog-has-more-freedom-palestinians-at-cyber-city-camp-for-refugees-from-syria%2F%5C%22%3EPalestinians%20displaced%20from%20Syria%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20whom%20movement%20and%20work%20opportunities%20have%20been%20severely%20restricted%20in%20Jordan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPalestinians%20living%20beyond%20Jordan%20also%20face%20distinct%20circumstances.%20In%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unrwa.org%2Fwhere-we-work%2Fwest-bank%5C%22%3Eapproximately%20900%2C000%20Palestinian%20refugees%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0live%20under%20Israeli%20occupation%2C%20subject%20to%20a%20discriminatory%20system%20that%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.btselem.org%2Fapartheid%5C%22%3Ehuman%20rights%20organizations%20have%20called%20%E