%20losses%20in%20the%20fight%2C%20its%20movement%20along%20a%20railway%20track%20that%20could%20allow%20them%20to%20regroup%20and%20concentrate%20forces%20%26quot%3Bis%20a%20very%20serious%20threat%20that%20needs%20maximum%20attention.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvdiivka%20has%20been%20largely%20ruined%20by%20constant%20fighting%2C%20but%20the%20devastated%20area%20may%20not%20be%20entirely%20pointless%20to%20Russian%20forces%2C%20or%20Russian%20leadership.%20The%20loss%20of%20Avdiivka%20would%20push%20Ukraine%20back%20from%20the%20threshold%20of%20Donetsk%2C%20making%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20launch%20attacks%20to%20retake%20the%20area.%20Russia%20would%20also%20be%20able%20to%20establish%20supply%20routes%20and%20connect%20main%20routes%20between%20its%20occupied%20territory%20if%20it%20had%20control%20of%20Avdiivka.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20the%20win%20could%20be%20valuable%20politically.%20Beyond%20Bakhmut%2C%20seen%20by%20many%20as%20a%20Pyrrhic%20victory%20at%20best%2C%20Russia%20has%20won%20few%20battlefield%20victories.%20And%20to%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%20it%20has%20seen%20a%20few%20tumultuous%20incidents%20occur%20throughout%20the%20year%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Wagner%20Group%20mutiny.%20With%20a%20presidential%20election%20coming%20in%20early%202024%2C%20it's%20possible%20that%20Putin%20has%20decided%20to%20prioritize%20taking%20Avdiivka%20in%20order%20to%20maintain%20the%20appearance%20of%20control%20and%20demonstrate%20capability%20as%20a%20leader%20to%20Russians%20watching%20friends%20and%20family%20die%20in%20a%20war%20he%20aggressively%20initiated%20and%20has%20had%20to%20conduct%20unwelcome%20mobilizations%20to%20feed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-paying-for-assault-on-avdiivka-heavy-vehicle-losses-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699044