0use%20of%20brominated%20vegetable%20oil%20in%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFood%20companies%20have%20used%20the%20additive%20BVO%20since%20the%201920s.%20For%20decades%2C%20manufacturers%20used%20it%20to%20keep%20fruit%20flavoring%20in%20a%20stable%20form%20that%20doesn't%20separate%20and%20rise%20to%20the%20top.%20It%20was%20used%20in%20some%20sodas%2C%20fruit%20juices%2C%20and%20other%20drinks%20with%20citrus%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20agency%20concluded%20that%20the%20intended%20use%20of%20BVO%20in%20food%20is%20no%20longer%20considered%20safe%20after%20the%20results%20of%20studies%20conducted%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20National%20Institutes%20of%20Health%20(NIH)%20found%20the%20potential%20for%20adverse%20health%20effects%20in%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20Jones%2C%20the%20FDA's%20deputy%20commissioner%20for%20human%20foods%2C%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fpress-announcements%2Ffda-proposes-ban-food-additive-continues-assessments-additional-chemicals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20the%20move%20follows%20a%20recent%20ban%20on%20the%20ingredient%20in%20California.%20In%20October%2C%20California%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.ca.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAB-418-Signing.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esigned%20a%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20prohibiting%20the%20sale%20of%20food%20or%20drink%20items%20with%20BVO%20and%20other%20ingredients%20like%20red%20dye%203%20and%20potassium%20bromate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDA%20is%20accepting%20comments%20on%20its%20proposal%20through%20January%2017%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20can%20you%20tell%20what%20drinks%20contain%20BVO%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201958%2C%20the%20FDA%20gained%20the%20authority%20to%20determine%20the%20safety%20of%20food%20ingredients.%20In%20the%20years%20following%2C%20it%20listed%20BVO%20as%20generally%20recognized%20as%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20new%20data%20showed%20potential%20health%20effects%2C%20and%20the%20FDA%20removed%20it%20from%20the%20GRAS%20list%20in%20the%20'60s.%20The%20agency%20limited%20its%20use%20to%20a%20stabilizer%20that%20couldn't%20exceed%20the%20level%20of%2015%20parts%20per%20million%20in%20the%20drinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDA%20notes%20that%20many%20beverage%20companies%20have%20since%20found%20alternative%20stabilizers.%20For%20example%2C%20in%202014%2C%20Coca-Cola%20announced%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoca-cola-removing-bvo-from-powerade-2014-5%5C%22%3Eremoving%20BVO%20from%20Powerade%3C%2Fa%3E%20drinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20you%20may%20still%20find%20BVO%20in%20some%20soft%20drinks%20or%20other%20fruit-flavored%20drinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20avoid%20BVO%2C%20you%20should%20check%20the%20ingredients%20in%20sodas%2C%20fruit%20drinks%2C%20lemonade%2C%20and%20juices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20used%2C%20BVO%20is%20required%20to%20be%20listed%20as%20an%20ingredient%20on%20the%20label%20as%20%26quot%3Bbrominated%20vegetable%20oil%26quot%3B%20or%20as%20the%20specific%20oil%20that%20has%20been%20brominated%2C%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bbrominated%20soybean%20oil%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%20data-stringify-type%3D%5C%22bold%5C%22%3EBVO%20side%20effects%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FDA%20has%20been%20monitoring%20the%20effects%20of%20BVO%20since%20the%201970s%2C%20after%20a%20report%20showed%20that%20it%20could%20cause%20heart%20problems%20when%20taken%20in%20large%20doses%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Ffood%2Ffood-additives-petitions%2Fbrominated-vegetable-oil-bvo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eagency's%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20decades%20since%2C%20sparse%20reports%20have%20emerged%20about%20its%20potential%20harms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20anecdotal%20reports%20of%20people%20visiting%20the%20hospital%20with%20telltale%20signs%20of%20bromine%20poisoning%20%E2%80%94%20headache%2C%20fatigue%2C%20memory%20loss%2C%20and%20problems%20walking.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F9140329%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20one%201997%20case%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20doctors%20determined%20that%20a%20patient%20had%20gotten%20the%20condition%20from%20drinking%202-4%20liters%20of%20soda%20with%20BVO%20in%20it%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBVO%20can%20also%20hurt%20the%20parts%20of%20your%20body%20used%20in%20eating%20and%20drinking%2C%20Katherine%20Zeratsky%2C%20a%20registered%20dietitian%20at%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foodnetwork.com%2Fhealthy%2Farticles%2Fbrominated-vegetable-oil-dangers-side-effects%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Food%20Network%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BHealth%20concerns%20about%20BVO%20stem%20from%20one%20of%20its%20ingredients%2C%20bromine.%20Bromine%20can%20irritate%20the%20skin%2C%20nose%2C%20mouth%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202022%20report%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Food%20and%20Chemical%20Toxicology%2C%20the%20FDA%20found%20that%20BVO%20may%20build%20up%20in%20mice%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthyroid-health-need-to-know-2018-8%5C%22%3Ethyroids%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20time%2C%20becoming%20toxic.%20Though%20they%20conducted%20these%20tests%20in%20mice%2C%20not%20humans%2C%20the%20agency%20deemed%20its%20results%20were%20significant%20enough%20to%20recommend%20against%20the%20use%20of%20BVO%20in%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20humans%2C%20thyroids%20help%20control%20blood%20pressure%2C%20temperature%2C%20heart%20rate%2C%20and%20metabolism.%20Thyroid%20damage%20can%20cause%20weight%20fluctuations%2C%20heart%20rate%20irregularity%2C%20decreased%20energy%2C%20poor%20bone%20health%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hopkinsmedicine.org%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-and-diseases%2Fdisorders-of-the-thyroid%23%3A~%3Atext%3DProblems%2520with%2520the%2520thyroid%2520include%2Cpregnancy%2520and%2520many%2520other%2520functions.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20more%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20results%20of%20the%20proposal%20won't%20be%20fully%20processed%20until%202024%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2023%2F11%2F02%2Fhealth%2Fbrominated-vegetable-oil-ban-fda-proposal-wellness%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECNN%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffda-brominated-vegetable-oil-bvo-soda-proposed-ban-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699044249000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65454e9f36d588dc55cabde1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffda-brominated-vegetable-oil-bvo-soda-proposed-ban-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Brominated%20vegetable%20oil%2C%20an%20additive%20in%20some%20US%20sodas%2C%20shouldn't%20be%20allowed%20in%20food%2C%20per%20new%20FDA%20recommendations.%20Here's%20why%20BVO%20is%20unsafe%20to%20drink.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmcgrath%40insider.com%20(Jenny%20McGrath%2CMaiya%20Focht)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffda-brominated-vegetable-oil-bvo-soda-proposed-ban-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amazon%20delivery%20drivers%20can%20make%20up%20to%20%2440K%20annual%20salary%2C%20plus%20benefits%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222222%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20delivery%20driver%20sits%20in%20drivers%20seat%20behind%2