ky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-scores-killed-and-injured-after-reported-attack-on-ambulance-convoy-in-gaza-12999623%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-scores-killed-and-injured-after-reported-attack-on-ambulance-convoy-in-gaza-12999623%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-scores-killed-and-injured-after-reported-attack-on-ambulance-convoy-in-gaza-12999623%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Delhi%20Air%20Quality%20in%20'Severe'%20Category%2C%20No%20Respite%20from%20Pollution%20in%20Sight%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F13184606%2FPollution.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20an%20%E2%80%9Cideal%E2%80%9D%20situation%2C%20Indian%20cricket%20captain%20Rohit%20Sharma%20said%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20November%201.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESharma%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20talking%20about%20losing%20a%20toss%20or%20a%20poor%20batting%20pitch.%20He%20was%20talking%20about%20the%20air%20quality%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20a%20day%20before%20India%20played%20Sri%20Lanka%20at%20the%20Wankhede%20Stadium%20in%20the%20city%2C%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%20that%20India%20is%20hosting.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDelhi%2C%20more%20than%201%2C400%20kilometres%20away%2C%20is%20also%20hosting%20World%20Cup%20matches.%20On%20November%206%2C%20the%20Arun%20Jaitley%20Stadium%20will%20witness%20a%20match%20between%20Bangladesh%20and%20Sri%20Lanka.%20But%20the%20air%20quality%20here%20is%20far%20worse%20than%20Mumbai%E2%80%99s.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20seen%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Bangladesh%20cricket%20team%20on%20Friday%20cancelled%20its%20training%20session%20in%20the%20national%20capital%20ahead%20of%20their%20match%20against%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20citing%20severe%20air%20pollution.%20Several%20players%20reportedly%20experienced%20respiratory%20discomfort%20and%20coughing%20due%20to%20the%20deteriorating%20air%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%201%2C%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20air%20quality%20was%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20poor%E2%80%9D%20category.%20On%20November%202%2C%20it%20made%20it%20to%20the%20higher%20rung%3A%20%E2%80%9Csevere%E2%80%9D.%20On%20Friday%2C%20November%203%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20at%20the%20upper%20extreme%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Csevere%E2%80%9D%20category.%20A%20smog%20hangs%20in%20the%20air.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20predictions%20for%20the%20days%20to%20come%20are%20not%20comforting.%20A%20Union%20government%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fews.tropmet.res.in%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eearly%20warning%20system%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20Delhi%20predicts%20that%20the%20air%20quality%20will%20remain%20in%20this%20category%20till%20November%206.%20And%20their%20outlook%20for%20the%20subsequent%20six%20days%20after%20that%20is%20worrying%20too%3A%20air%20quality%20is%20likely%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Csevere%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20poor%E2%80%9D%20category.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EDelhi%E2%80%99s%20winter%20woes%20have%20begun.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Very%20poor%E2%80%99%20to%20%E2%80%98severe%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20start%20of%20every%20Delhi%20winter%20now%20marks%20the%20beginning%20of%20months%20of%20poor%20air%20quality.%20Several%20factors%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fexplainer-delhis-air-quality-dips-but-only-weather-conditions-to-blame-yet%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econtribute%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20this%2C%20studies%20have%20shown%3A%20from%20farmers%20in%20Delhi%20NCR%20and%20the%20neighbouring%20states%20of%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20burning%20crop%20residue%20to%20prepare%20their%20fields%20faster%20for%20a%20new%20sowing%20season%2C%20to%20emissions%20released%20by%20the%20burning%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20used%20in%20industries%20and%20vehicles.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20pollutants%20released%20by%20the%20latter%20include%20particulate%20matter%20(PM)%20which%20are%20inhalable%20particles%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20emissions.%20Particulate%20matter%20can%20vary%20in%20size%3A%20ranging%20from%20fine%20diameters%20of%202.5%20mm%20(called%20PM2.5)%20to%20larger%20ones%20of%20diameters%20of%20around%2010%20mm%20(PM10).%20In%20India%2C%20the%20current%20annual%20average%20safe%20limits%20for%20PM2.5%20and%20PM10%20set%20by%20the%20CPCB%20are%2040%20micrograms%2Fper%20cubic%20metre%20(ug%2Fm3)%20and%2060%20ug%2Fm3%20respectively%2C%20far%20higher%20than%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fsci-tech%2Fhealth%2Fwho-tightens-global-air-quality-norms%2Farticle36617490.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estandards%20set%20by%20the%20WHO%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03220809%2F1200px-Low_visibility_due_to_Smog_in_entry_of_Chelmsford_Road_New_Delhi_31st_Dec_2017_9AM_DSCN8819_1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221199%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03220809%2F1200px-Low_visibility_due_to_Smog_in_entry_of_Chelmsford_Road_New_Delhi_31st_Dec_2017_9AM_DSCN8819_1.jpg%201199w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03220809%2F1200px-Low_visibility_due_to_Smog_in_entry_of_Chelmsford_Road_New_Delhi_31st_Dec_2017_9AM_DSCN8819_1-300x223.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03220809%2F1200px-Low_visibility_due_to_Smog_in_entry_of_Chelmsford_Road_New_Delhi_31st_Dec_2017_9AM_DSCN8819_1-1024x760.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683413%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22890%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFile%20photo.%20Low%20visibility%20due%20to%20Smog%20at%20the%20entry%20of%20Chelmsford%20Road%20New%20Delhi%20on%20December%2031%2C%202017%2C%20at%209%20am.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FSumita%20Roy%20Dutta%2FCC%20BY-SA%204.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeteorological%20conditions%20play%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fexplainer-delhis-air-quality-dips-but-only-weather-conditions-to-blame-yet%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erole%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20too%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20high%20air%20pollution%20levels%3A%20when%20wind%20speeds%20slow%20down%2C%20particulate%20matter%20stays%20suspended%20in%20the%20atmosphere%2C%20contributing%20to%20the%20worsening%20air%20quality.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20instance%2C%20on%20Sunday%2C%20Punjab%20saw%20a%20740%25%20increase%20in%20farm%20fires%2C%20with%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20recorded%20in%20a%20single%20day%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fnov%2F03%2Fdelhi-india-air-quality-pollution-spike-world-health-organization-limit%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20Central%20Pollution%20Control%20Board%E2%80%99s%20(CPCB)%20official%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpcb.nic.in%2F%2Fupload%2FDownloads%2FAQI_Bulletin_20231103.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eestimate%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20November%203%2C%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Air%20Quality%20Index%20was%20468%20and%20the%20prominent%20pollutants%20were%20both%20PM2.5%20and%20PM10.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20what%20does%20this%20number%20mean%3F%20India%E2%80%99s%20Air%20Quality%20Index%2C%20or%20AQI%2C%20is%20a%20measure%20of%20levels%20of%20at%20least%20three%20pollutants%2C%20one%20of%20them%20being%20particulate%20matter.%20The%20Index%20ranges%20from%200%20to%20500.%20An%20AQI%20between%200%20to%2050%20is%20considered%20ideal%2C%20healthy.%20If%20your%20city%20has%20an%20AQI%20between%2051%20and%20100%20(categorised%20as%20%E2%80%9Csatisfactory%E2%80%9D)%2C%20the%20air%20you%20breathe%20could%20cause%20%E2%80%9Cminor%20breathing%20discomfort%20to%20sensitive%20people%E2%80%9D%2C%20per%20the%20CPCB.%20But%20the%20higher%20the%20AQI%2C%20the%20worse%20the%20category%20gets%2C%20as%20do%20the%20impacts%20of%20such%20air%20on%20even%20healthy%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EProlonged%20exposure%20to%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20poor%E2%80%9D%20air%20quality%20can%20cause%20respiratory%20illnesses%2C%20as%20per%20India%E2%80%99s%20Central%20Pollution%20Control%20Board%20(CPCB).%20%E2%80%9CSevere%E2%80%9D%20is%20indicative%20of%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20air%20pollution%20%E2%80%93%20it%20can%20not%20only%20have%20serious%20impacts%20on%20people%20with%20existing%20diseases%2C%20but%20also%20affect%20healthy%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20where%20Delhi%20is%20now.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%207%3A48%20pm%20on%20November%203%2C%20Delhi%20ranked%20second%20%E2%80%93%20just%20two%20points%20below%20Lahore%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iqair.com%2Fin-en%2Fworld-air-quality-ranking%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eworld%E2%80%99s%20most%20polluted%20city%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20based%20on%20Swiss%20agency%20IQAIR%E2%80%99s%20live%20rankings.%20(The%20IQAir%20index%20is%20calculated%20differently.)%20Among%20Indian%20cities%2C%20Delhi%20topped%20the%20IQAir%20list.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20pollution%20level%20will%20continue%20for%20the%20next%20two%20to%20three%20weeks%2C%20%E2%80%9Caggravated%20by%20incidents%20of%20stubble%20burning%2C%20slow%20wind%20speed%20and%20cooling%20temperatures%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EReuters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Fair-pollution-indias-new-delhi-turns-severe-some-schools-shut-2023-11-03%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Equoted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Ashwani%20Kumar%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Pollution%20Control%20Committee%2C%20as%20saying%20on%20November%203.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ministry%20of%20earth%20sciences%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fews.tropmet.res.in%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAir%20Quality%20Early%20Warning%20System%20for%20Delhi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(a%20project%20under%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Tropical%20Meteorology%20Pune)%20predicts%20that%20the%20air%20quality%20will%20likely%20be%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cupper%20end%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Csevere%E2%80%9D%20category%20on%20November%203%20%E2%80%93%20and%20remain%20in%20this%20category%20till%20November%206.%20Their%20outlook%20for%20the%20subsequent%20six%20days%20after%20that%20is%20worrying%20too%2C%20with%20the%20early%20warning%20system%20predicting%20that%20the%20air%20quality%20is%20likely%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9CSevere%E2%80%9D%20to%20%E2%80%9CVery%20Poor%E2%80%9D%20category.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIncreasing%20evidence%20of%20impacts%20on%20health%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncreasing%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20poor%20air%20quality%20has%20numerous%20impacts%20on%20human%20as%20well%20as%20environmental%20health.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFine%20particulate%20matter%20(PM2.5)%2C%20absorbed%20through%20the%20human%20respiratory%20system%2C%20can%20reach%20the%20bloodstream%20and%20cause%20numerous%20respiratory%20illnesses.%20According%20to%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC9223652%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estudy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202022%2C%20the%20latest%20data%20shows%20that%20PM2.5%20is%20responsible%20for%20nearly%204%20million%20deaths%20globally%20from%20cardiopulmonary%20illnesses%20including%20heart%20disease%2C%20chronic%20lung%20disease%2C%20cancers%20and%20preterm%20births.%20Both%20ambient%20(outdoor)%20and%20household%20(indoor)%20air%20pollution%20are%20responsible%20for%20about%207%20million%20deaths%20globally%20per%20year%2C%20per%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fwesternpacific%2Fhealth-topics%2Fair-pollution%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWHO%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrc.bmj.com%2Fcontent%2Fbmjdrc%2F11%2F5%2Fe003333.full.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estudy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20published%20in%20October%20this%20year%20found%20that%20inhaling%20air%20with%20high%20amounts%20of%20PM2.5%20led%20to%20high%20blood%20sugar%20levels%20and%20increased%20incidences%20of%20Type%20II%20diabetes%20in%20adults.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%20during%20the%20World%20Cup%2C%20Joe%20Root%20had%20brought%20up%20the%20issue%20of%20air%20quality%20after%20South%20Africa%20defeated%20England%20in%20Mumbai.%20ESPNCricInfo%20quoted%20him%20as%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20like%20%E2%80%9Cyou%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20get%20your%20breath%E2%80%A6%20It%20was%20like%20you%20were%20eating%20the%20air.%20It%20was%20unique.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAir%20pollution%20impacts%20children%20adversely%20too.%20A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0048969721078347%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estudy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202022%20by%20a%20team%20including%20scientists%20from%20IIT%20Delhi%20found%20a%20strong%20relationship%20between%20ambient%20air%20pollution%20and%20infant%20mortality%20(death%20of%20children%20under%20five%20years%20of%20age)%20in%20India%20when%20they%20studied%20the%20data%20on%20particulate%20matter%20(PM2.5)%20from%20satellite%20imagery%2C%20and%20data%20from%20the%20Demographic%20and%20Health%20Survey%20of%20India%20of%202015-2016.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDr.%20Naveen%20Thacker%2C%20president%20of%20the%20International%20Pediatric%20Association%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fphase-out-fossil-fuels-46-million-healthcare-professionals-cop28-presidency%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etold%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20November%201%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20well-known%20fact%E2%80%9D%20that%20air%20pollution%20adversely%20impacts%20children%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20%5Bdoctors%5D%20are%20seeing%20that%20in%20our%20practice%20now%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20political%20blame%20game%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20political%20parties%20have%20taken%20to%20blaming%20each%20other%20for%20each%20other%20for%20failing%20to%20tackle%20the%20drastic%20drops%20in%20air%20quality%20levels%20that%20the%20national%20capital%20witnesses%20every%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CBJP%E2%80%99s%20politics%20reeks%20of%20hypocrisy%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPTI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FPTI_News%2Fstatus%2F1720387260187582568%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Equoted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20AAP%20MLA%20Saurabh%20Bharadwaj%20as%20saying%20on%20November%203.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20are%20the%20governments%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Haryana%20doing%20related%20to%20air%20pollution%20that%20is%20prevailing%20across%20north%20India%3F%20It%20is%20only%20the%20government%20of%20Delhi%20that%20has%20taken%20measures%20to%20control%20air%20pollution%20and%20is%20accountable%20to%20the%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03221319%2F5543835085_0c31bddd3e_k.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03221319%2F5543835085_0c31bddd3e_k.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03221319%2F5543835085_0c31bddd3e_k-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03221319%2F5543835085_0c31bddd3e_k-1024x684.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683417%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22801%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFile%20photo.%20View%20of%20West%20Delhi.%20Photo%3A%20flickr.com%2FJean-Etienne%20Minh-Duy%20Poirrier%2F%20CC%20BY-SA%202.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBJP%20national%20spokesperson%20Shehzad%20Poonawalla%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20accused%20the%20Kejriwal-led%20AAP%20government%20in%20Delhi%20of%20inaction.%20%E2%80%9CQuestions%20must%20be%20asked%20from%20the%20Kejriwal%20government%20about%20what%20it%20has%20done%20in%20the%20last%207-8%20years%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20air%20pollution%20in%20Delhi%2C%E2%80%9D%20PTI%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FPTI_News%2Fstatus%2F1720337086740398173%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Equoted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20him%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDelhi%20Pradesh%20Congress%20Committee%20chief%20Arvinder%20Singh%20Lovely%20said%20that%20the%20Delhi%20government%20should%20have%20taken%20measures%20to%20control%20air%20pollution%2015%20days%20ago.%20%E2%80%9CInfrastructure%20projects%20are%20delayed%20while%20the%20public%20transport%20system%20has%20collapsed%20leading%20to%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20usage%20of%20private%20vehicles%20in%20the%20city%20contributing%20to%20air%20pollution%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FPTI_News%2Fstatus%2F1720387260187582568%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPTI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECongress%20leader%20and%20former%20environment%20minister%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20quoted%20studies%20to%20highlight%20the%20urgency%20for%20action%20in%20dealing%20with%20air%20pollution%20in%20the%20national%20capital.%20He%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FJairam_Ramesh%2Fstatus%2F1720064225790546127%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Equoted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20two%20studies%20that%20show%20that%20higher%20PM2.5%20levels%20increase%20both%20Type%20II%20diabetes%20and%20hypertension.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Modi%20govt%20has%20tried%20hard%20to%20discredit%20past%20studies%20that%20clearly%20linked%20increased%20disease%20burden%20in%20India%20to%20air%20pollution.%20But%20it%20cannot%20wish%20away%20these%20two%20studies%20and%20the%20air%20pollution%20crisis%20at%20large.%20The%20time%20to%20act%20is%20well%20past.%20For%20the%20sake%20of%20future%20generations%20we%20NEED%20drastic%20measures%20NOW%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FJairam_Ramesh%2Fstatus%2F1720064225790546127%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etweeted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20November%202.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThe%20Indian%20cricket%20captain%20has%20very%20rightly%20raised%20serious%20concerns%20on%20the%20worsening%20air%20pollution%20situation%20in%20India%2C%20which%20has%20now%20extended%20far%20beyond%20North%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%