al%20attended%20both%20the%20monsoon%20session%20and%20parliament%E2%80%99s%20special%20session%20that%20passed%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%2C%20where%20he%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20legislation%20along%20with%20the%20other%20NCP%20MPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20on%20October%209%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Hrishikesh%20Roy%20and%20Sanjay%20Karol%20stayed%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F1058582%2Fmohammad-faizals-lok-sabha-membership-restored-again%5C%22%3Ethe%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20August%2022%20order%20in%20the%20matter%20would%20take%20effect.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20order%20specified%20that%20the%20benefit%20of%20suspension%20of%20Faizal%E2%80%99s%20conviction%20would%20continue%20while%20the%20matter%20was%20remanded%20to%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699017315000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F14133347%2FUntitled-design-13.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Flakshadweep-lok-sabha-mp-mohammed-faizal-reinstated-for-the-second-time%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20NCP%20leader%20was%20disqualified%20on%20October%204%20for%20the%20second%20time%20after%20the%20Kerala%20high%20court%20refused%20to%20stay%20his%20conviction%20in%20the%202009%20case.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Flakshadweep-lok-sabha-mp-mohammed-faizal-reinstated-for-the-second-time%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Annual%20Report%20on%20Digital%20Labour%20Platforms%20Shows%20Worker%20Pay%20Is%20Largely%20Below%20Living%20Wage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F11165805%2FScreen-Shot-2019-09-11-at-4.57.43-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Zero%20of%20the%2012%20digital%20labour%20platforms%20evaluated%20in%20the%20Fairwork%20India%202023%20report%20showed%20evidence%20of%20providing%20their%20workers%20with%20a%20living%20wage.%20Only%20three%20of%20the%2012%20%E2%80%94%20bigbasket%2C%20Flipkart%20and%20Urban%20Company%20%E2%80%94%20ensured%20the%20local%20minimum%20wage%20after%20work-related%20costs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20no%20platform%20to%20ensure%20fair%20representation%20for%20their%20workers%2C%20meaning%20platforms%20did%20not%20provide%20a%20process%20through%20which%20workers%20could%20express%20their%20voices%20collectively%2C%20such%20as%20through%20recognised%20trade%20unions%20or%20collective%20bodies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CRepresentation%20through%20a%20collective%20body%20or%20trade%20union%20is%20a%20vital%20dimension%20of%20fairness%20at%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20Fairwork%20said.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20disconcerting%20that%20despite%20the%20rise%20in%20platform%20worker%20collectivisation%20across%20the%20country%2C%20over%20the%20past%20four%20years%2C%20there%20was%20insufficient%20evidence%20from%20any%20platform%20that%20showed%20a%20willingness%20to%20recognise%20a%20collective%20body%20of%20workers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFairwork%20evaluated%20the%20working%20conditions%20of%20gig%20workers%20at%20Amazon%20Flex%2C%20bigbasket%2C%20BluSmart%2C%20Dunzo%2C%20Flipkart%2C%20Ola%2C%20Porter%2C%20Swiggy%2C%20Uber%2C%20Urban%20Company%2C%20Zepto%20and%20Zomato%20using%20five%20principles%3A%20fair%20pay%2C%20fair%20conditions%2C%20fair%20contracts%2C%20fair%20management%20and%20fair%20representation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20desk%20research%20and%20359%20worker%20interviews%20across%20Bengaluru%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Kochi%20and%20Thiruvananthapuram%2C%20platforms%20were%20graded%20on%20a%2010-point%20scale.%20Under%20each%20principle%2C%20companies%20could%20receive%20two%20points.%20This%20year%2C%20no%20platform%20scored%20higher%20than%20six%20points.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20fair%20conditions%2C%2010%20platforms%20received%20the%20first%20point%20for%20%E2%80%9Cproviding%20adequate%20safety%20equipment%20and%20periodic%20safety%20training%20to%20their%20workers.%E2%80%9D%20A%20second%20point%20was%20given%20to%20five%20platforms%20for%20providing%20workers%20with%20accident%20insurance%20coverage%20at%20no%20additional%20cost%2C%20compensating%20workers%20for%20income%20lost%20due%20to%20medical%20leave%20and%20for%20ensuring%20that%20workers%E2%80%99%20standing%20was%20not%20negatively%20affected%20after%20returning%20to%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20fair%20contracts%2C%20seven%20platforms%20%E2%80%94%20bigbasket%2C%20BluSmart%2C%20Dunzo%2C%20Swiggy%2C%20Urban%20Company%2C%20Zepto%20and%20Zomato%20%E2%80%94%20were%20awarded%20the%20first%20point%20for%20ensuring%20their%20contracts%20were%20accessible%20and%20comprehensible%2C%20and%20for%20having%20a%20protocol%20for%20data%20protection%20and%20management.%20Five%20met%20the%20requirements%20for%20the%20second%20point%20that%20required%20more%20transparent%20and%20clarifying%20language%20in%20worker%20contracts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20fair%20management%2C%20Amazon%20Flex%2C%20bigbasket%2C%20BluSmart%2C%20Flipkart%2C%20Swiggy%2C%20and%20Zomato%20were%20awarded%20the%20first%20point%20for%20providing%20due%20process%20in%20decisions%20affecting%20workers%20and%20maintaining%20channels%20for%20workers%20to%20appeal%20disciplinary%20actions.%20Only%20BluSmart%20and%20Swiggy%20received%20a%20second%20point%20for%20regulating%20external%20audits%20to%20check%20for%20biases%20in%20how%20work%20is%20allocated%20among%20workers%20and%20for%20adopting%20anti-discrimination%20policies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEach%20year%2C%20the%20report%20focuses%20on%20a%20different%20theme.%20This%20year%2C%20the%20theme%20was%20discrimination%20and%20alienation%20felt%20by%20platform%20workers.%20Fairwork%20said%20the%20lack%20of%20provisions%20in%20place%20for%20fair%20representation%20and%20workers%E2%80%99%20inability%20to%20influence%20how%20platforms%20address%20collective%20issues%20has%20contributed%20to%20alienation%20or%20estrangement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFairwork%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20alienation%20is%20deeply%20intertwined%20with%20the%20discrimination%20that%20platform%20workers%20face%20due%20to%20social%20identities%20such%20as%20caste%2C%20class%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20religion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20a%20national%20scale%2C%20Fairwork%20said%202023%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmilestone%20year%20for%20platform%20workers%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20This%20year%2C%20the%20Rajasthan%20Platform%20Based%20Gig%20Workers%20(Registration%20and%20Welfare)%20Act%2C%202023%20was%20passed%2C%20which%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eregulates%20the%20engagement%20of%20platform-based%20gig%20workers%20and%20aims%20to%20provide%20them%20with%20social%20security%20and%20other%20benefits.%20The%20legislation%20came%20after%20years%20of%20platform%20workers%20organizing%20for%20their%20rights%20and%20raising%20claims%20with%20the%20State.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20rules%20for%20implementing%20the%20Rajasthan%20Act%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20framed%2C%20the%20act%20marks%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20providing%20social%20security%20to%20platform%20workers%2C%E2%80%9D%20Fairwork%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Declaration%20at%20the%20G20%20summit%2C%20held%20on%20September%209%20and%2010%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20also%20called%20to%20ensure%20%E2%80%9Cadequate%20social%20protection%20and%20decent%20working%20conditions%20for%20gig%20and%20platform%20workers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20year%20that%20has%20seen%20the%20formulation%20of%20a%20significant%20regulation%20based%20on%20inputs%20from%20workers%2C%20we%20hope%20that%20highlighting%20the%20experiences%20of%20workers%20will%20point%20to%20the%20structural%20changes%20that%20platforms%2C%20consumers%20and%20the%20State%20alike%20will%20need%20to%20undertake%20if%20the%20platform%20economy%20is%20to%20offer%20its%20workers%20decent%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Professors%20Balaji%20Parthasarathy%20and%20Janaki%20Srinivasan%2C%20the%20principal%20investigators%20of%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%20to%20interviewing%20workers%2C%20the%20Fairwork%20India%202023%20report%20included%20a%20survey%20of%20963%20consumers%20across%20the%2012%20platforms%20to%20gauge%20consumer%20awareness%20of%20the%20working%20conditions%20of%20platform%20workers.%20Fairwork%20said%20in%20the%20largest%20cities%20surveyed%2C%20there%20was%20significant%20support%20for%20bringing%20change%20to%20working%20conditions%20in%20the%20platform%20economy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CConsumers%20can%20use%20these%20scores%20to%20make%20informed%20decisions%20about%20which%20platforms%20to%20use%2C%E2%80%9D%20Fairwork%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20scores%20can%20serve%20as%20additional%20resources%20for%20collective%20worker%20bodies%20when%20they%20raise%20demands.%20We%20also%20hope%20that%20the%20findings%20of%20this%20report%20will%20provide%20regulators%20with%20a%20basis%20to%20formulate%20policies%20for%20the%20platform%20economy%20in%20consultation%20with%20other%20stakeholders%2C%20including%20workers%2C%20platforms%20and%20venture%20capitalists.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699016437000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F11165805%2FScreen-Shot-2019-09-11-at-4.57.43-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fannual-report-on-digital-labour-platforms-shows-worker-pay-is-largely-below-living-wage%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fairwork%20India%20has%20released%20its%205th%20annual%20study%2C%20focusing%20on%20the%20discrimination%20and%20alienation%20felt%20by%20platform%20workers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fannual-report-on-digital-labour-platforms-shows-worker-pay-is-largely-below-living-wage%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres%20in%20Nepal%3A%20Transitional%20Justice%20to%20the%20Fore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153658%2FF9m-3Tka4AAyqdf.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKathmandu%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Many%20observers%20found%20it%20intriguing%20that%20UN%20secretary-general%20Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres%20would%20want%20to%20spend%20three%20full%20days%20in%20Nepal%20even%20as%20Israel%20was%20carpet-bombing%20Gaza.%3Cbr%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20did%20speak%20out%20from%20the%20Security%20Council%20floor%2C%20for%20which%20he%20was%20rewarded%20with%20a%20demand%20for%20resignation%20by%20the%20Israeli%20ambassador%2C%20but%20there%20was%20obviously%20much%20more%20to%20be%20done%20against%20the%20ongoing%20mass%20murder%20of%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20Nepali%20commentator%20asked%20on%20Twitter%2C%20%E2%80%9CIs%20this%20the%20time%20for%20the%20UN%20secretary%20general%20to%20be%20anywhere%20other%20than%20the%20Middle%20East%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20it%20was%20the%20prospect%20of%20visiting%20Lumbini%2C%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Sakyamuni%20Siddhartha%20Gautam%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Buddha%2C%20Asia%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98prince%20of%20peace%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20that%20brought%20Guterres%20to%20Nepal.%20He%20did%20use%20his%20time%20at%20the%20nativity%20site%2C%20which%20has%20been%20visited%20by%20all%20five%20secretaries-general%20since%20Dag%20Hammarskjold%20in%201959%2C%20to%20highlight%20the%20urgency%20of%20world%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20secretary-general%20might%20also%20have%20wanted%20to%20laud%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20role%20as%20the%20second-largest%20contributor%20to%20UN%20peacekeeping%20operations%2C%20a%20position%20it%20holds%20despite%20being%20kept%20off%20the%20command%20responsibilities%20it%20deserves.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20were%20two%20issues%20besides%20world%20peace%20that%20Guterres%20clearly%20wanted%20to%20highlight%3A%20the%20transforming%20world%20climate%2C%20and%20Nepal%20as%20a%20path-breaker%20in%20the%20arena%20of%20transitional%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20separate%20helicopter%20trips%20to%20the%20base%20of%20Mount%20Everest%20and%20the%20Annapurna%20Sanctuary%2C%20the%20secretary-general%20relied%20on%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20mountain%20people%20to%20sound%20the%20alarm%20on%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20three%20weeks%20before%20COP%2028%20is%20to%20start%20in%20Dubai.%20The%20highly%20populated%20%E2%80%98third%20pole%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20planet%20indeed%20serves%20as%20a%20barometer%20of%20global%20warming%2C%20and%20the%20receding%20glaciers%20of%20an%20inhabited%20Himalaya%20are%20a%20more%20potent%20bellwether%20of%20climate%20catastrophe%20than%20the%20Arctic%20or%20Antarctica.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJoint%20session%20of%20parliament%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20Nepal%2C%20the%20most%20significant%20aspect%20of%20the%20Secretary-General%E2%80%99s%20visit%20was%20the%20suspended%20transitional%20justice%20(TJ)%20process%2C%20which%20began%20with%20the%20end%20of%20the%20decade-long%20Maoist%20insurgency%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20languishes%20even%20though%20the%20Maoist%20rebels%20have%20long%20since%20joined%20mainstream%20politics%20and%20the%20commandant%20of%20the%20Maoist%20force%20is%20presently%20the%20prime%20minister.%20He%20is%20in%20that%20position%20despite%20holding%20no%20more%20than%2011%25%20of%20seats%20in%20parliament%2C%20but%20that%20is%20another%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Pushpa%20Kamal%20Dahal%20(nom%20de%20guerre%3A%20%E2%80%98Prachanda%E2%80%99)%20had%20hoped%20to%20use%20the%20secretary-general%E2%80%99s%20trip%20to%20show%20off%20his%20international%20standing%20to%20the%20Nepali%20populace%2C%20and%20to%20get%20a%20green%20signal%20from%20the%20secretary-general%20for%20his%20tendentious%20plans%20to%20push%20a%20perpetrator-friendly%20TJ%20draft%20law%20through%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20an%20overwhelming%20show%20of%20obsequiousness%20from%20Dahal%20who%20followed%20him%20at%20practically%20every%20step%20around%20the%20country%2C%20the%20secretary-general%20did%20not%20oblige%20his%20host.%20Instead%2C%20Guterres%20used%20every%20pulpit%20during%20his%20trip%20to%20insist%20that%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20TJ%20process%20be%20concluded%20within%20three%20parameters%3A%20a)%20concurrence%20of%20the%20victims%20of%20conflict%3B%20b)%20concordance%20with%20relevant%20international%20law%20and%20principles%3B%20and%2C%20c)%20following%20the%20precedence-setting%20judgements%20on%20transitional%20justice%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20victims%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20conflict%20did%20not%20get%20to%20meet%20the%20secretary-general%2C%20as%20requested%2C%20their%20various%20submissions%20were%20put%20together%20in%20a%20file%20and%20presented%20to%20Guterres%20as%20he%20departed%20for%20the%20airport%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20November%201%20by%20Hanaa%20Singer-Hamdy%2C%20the%20UN%20Resident%20Coordinator%20to%20Nepal.%20She%20said%20in%20her%20comment%20on%20X%20(Twitter)%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20needs%20and%20priorities%20of%20the%20conflict%20victims%20are%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20Transitional%20Justice-related%20discussion%20in%20Nepal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153718%2FF90eJxcbQAAIHll.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153718%2FF90eJxcbQAAIHll.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153718%2FF90eJxcbQAAIHll-300x196.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153718%2FF90eJxcbQAAIHll-1024x670.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683363%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22785%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHanaa%20Singer-Hamdy%20hands%20over%20the%20memorandum%20submitted%20by%20various%20conflict%20victims%20organisations%20to%20Antonio%20Guterres.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40SingerHanaa%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20of%20An%20Exemplary%20Process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20secretary-general%20clearly%20understands%20that%2C%20worldwide%2C%20the%20fraught%20arena%20of%20transitional%20justice%20has%20had%20too%20few%20successes%2C%20whereas%20it%20provides%20the%20pathway%20for%20post-conflict%20societies%20to%20heal%20and%20recover%20%E2%80%93%20through%20reparation%2C%20memorialisation%2C%20truth%20and%20reconciliation%2C%20not%20to%20forget%20accountability%20for%20extreme%20cases%20of%20human%20rights%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHerein%20lies%20the%20importance%20of%20Nepal%2C%20where%20the%20Nepali-led%20transitional%20justice%20process%20is%20presently%20stuck%2C%20but%20the%20victims%20and%20rights%20defenders%20have%20not%20let%20go.%20The%20international%20community%2C%20and%20especially%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20can%20help%20by%20ensuring%20that%20there%20is%20principled%20monitoring.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20Nepali%20players%20are%20capable%20of%20moving%20the%20boat%20to%20the%20other%20shore%20was%20what%20Guterres%20emphasised%20in%20his%20address%20on%20October%2031%20to%20a%20joint%20session%20of%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENepal%E2%80%99s%20transitional%20justice%20process%20could%20become%20an%20example%20for%20post-conflict%20societies%20the%20way%20Colombia%2C%20South%20Africa%20and%20Sierra%20Leone%20are%20today%20held%20out%20for%20their%20relative%20success.%20Within%20South%20Asia%2C%20a%20region%20awash%20in%20long-term%20conflict%20from%20Kashmir%20to%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Balochistan%20to%20the%20Arakan%2C%20transitional%20justice%20is%20not%20%E2%80%98deployed%E2%80%99%20anywhere%20else%20other%20than%20in%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20more%20reason%20for%20the%20Nepali%20process%20to%20succeed%20in%20order%20to%20provide%20a%20model%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20region%20to%20consider%2C%20and%20for%20Guterres%20to%20dwell%20on%20the%20matter%20during%20his%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20the%20main%20roadblock%20to%20a%20proper%20conclusion%20of%20the%20peace%20process%20was%20the%20secretary-general%E2%80%99s%20host%2C%20the%20prime%20minister.%20While%20Dahal%20used%20the%20conflict%20and%20the%20ensuing%20peace%20process%20to%20build%20his%20personal%20political%20career%2C%20he%20understands%20that%20a%20genuine%20transitional%20justice%20exercise%20would%20jeopardise%20his%20trajectory%20and%20pre-eminent%20position%20in%20Nepali%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20superstructure%20of%20his%20Maoist%20party%20would%20collapse%20were%20he%20to%20submit%20his%20colleagues%20to%20an%20accountability%20process%2C%20even%20if%20only%20%E2%80%98emblematic%20cases%E2%80%99%20were%20to%20be%20investigated.%20Hence%2C%20the%20formula%20used%20on%20the%20TJ%20over%20a%20decade%20and%20more%20has%20been%20prevarication%20and%20duplicity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20security%20personnel%20who%20would%20have%20been%20involved%20in%20atrocities%20during%20the%20conflict%20of%201995-2006%20are%20all%20retired%20by%20now%2C%20whereas%20the%20Maoist%20leadership%20is%20today%20part%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20political%20establishment%2C%20ruling%20the%20roost.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20loathe%20to%20be%20held%20accountable%2C%20which%20is%20why%20their%20supremo%20Dahal%20cannot%20countenance%20an%20honest%20exercise%2C%20and%20which%20is%20why%20he%20was%20hoping%20to%20bamboozle%20Guterres%20with%20pomp%20and%20flattery.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVictims%20and%20spoilers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20has%20historically%20been%20ferocious%20bloodletting%20in%20the%20Kathmandu%20court%20among%20clans%20and%20factions%20vying%20for%20power%2C%20and%20also%20during%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98unification%20exercise%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20villages%20of%20Nepal%20have%20been%20largely%20free%20of%20internecine%20violence%20until%20the%20decade%20of%20insurgency%20and%20state%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20villagers%20of%20Nepal%20were%20caught%20in%20a%20pincer%20between%20the%20Maoist%20rebels%20who%20specialised%20in%20hit-and-run%20raids%20and%20the%20security%20forces%20that%20meted%20out%20harsh%20treatment%20to%20local-level%20political%20leaders%2C%20teachers%20and%20development%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDahal%E2%80%99s%20role%20may%20be%20held%20up%20for%20scrutiny%20in%20a%20genuine%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20process%2C%20for%20he%20headed%20the%20chain%20of%20command%20of%20the%20Maoist%20insurgents.%20His%20attitude%20to%20atrocities%20including%20murder%2C%20torture%2C%20rape%20and%20abduction%20conducted%20by%20his%20cadre%20has%20always%20been%20ambiguous%2C%20and%20there%20has%20been%20no%20expression%20of%20remorse%20throughout%20his%20years%20in%20open%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20anything%2C%20there%20has%20been%20gleeful%20celebration%20of%20extra-judicial%20killing%20and%20physical%20violence%20generally%2C%20and%20he%20has%20even%20expressed%20satisfaction%20with%20how%20he%20personally%20fooled%20the%20United%20Nations%20Mission%20in%20Nepal%20(UNMIN)%20into%20tripling%20the%20number%20of%20Maoist%20combatants%20in%20a%20verification%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20upon%20coming%20above%20ground%2C%20Dahal%20told%20a%20BBC%20interlocutor%20that%20in%20a%20personal%20circular%20during%20the%20conflict%2C%20he%20had%20instructed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cyou%20may%20eliminate%20individuals%20if%20required%2C%20but%20without%20torture%E2%80%9D.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20Dahal%20has%20been%20the%20key%20leader%20who%20ensured%20that%20successive%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commissions%20were%20designed%20for%20failure%2C%20with%20their%20membership%20padded%20with%20Maoists.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20recently%2C%20Dahal%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20has%20been%20to%20push%20through%20legislation%20that%20would%20make%20it%20easy%20for%20the%20next%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20to%20let%20perpetrators%20(of%20both%20sides%2C%20rebels%20and%20state%20security)%20off%20the%20hook%20by%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20creating%20two%20categories%20of%20murder%3A%20%E2%80%98normal%20murder%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98extreme%20murder%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20the%20secretary-general%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20transitional%20justice%20efforts%20vitally%20important%20is%20that%20the%20Western%20governments%20and%20INGOs%20who%20introduced%20the%20concept%20and%20funded%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20engagement%20with%20TJ%20are%20now%20losing%20interest.%20This%20seems%20to%20have%20to%20do%20with%20%E2%80%98TJ%20fatigue%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20paucity%20of%20funding%2C%20as%20well%20as%20certain%20geopolitical%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20Western%20policymakers%20see%20Dahal%20as%20a%20pliable%20head%20of%20government%20of%20a%20strategically%20important%20Asian%20country%20that%20they%20must%20have%20%E2%80%98on%20their%20side%E2%80%99%20as%20China%20proceeds%20with%20a%20more%20aggressive%20continental%20policy%20of%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENepal%E2%80%99s%20victims%20of%20conflict%2C%20in%20coordination%20with%20human%20rights%20defenders%2C%20have%20been%20fighting%20a%20lonely%20battle%20against%20a%20political%20class%20and%20polity%20that%20have%20been%20in%20thrall%20of%20the%20Maoists%E2%80%99%20momentum%20and%20their%20attempt%20to%20create%20a%20%E2%80%98new%20normal%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20polity%2C%20with%20a%20forced%20attempt%20to%20ensure%20past%20atrocities%20are%20forgotten.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhereas%2C%20the%20victims%20of%20conflict%20are%20united%20in%20not%20letting%20the%20perpetrators%20get%20the%20better%20of%20memory.%20The%20UN%20secretary-general%20has%20come%20up%20with%20a%20powerful%20position%20of%20support%20for%20a%20transitional%20justice%20process%20that%20is%20just%20and%20humane%2C%20and%20the%20victim%20representatives%20and%20rights%20defenders%20of%20Kathmandu%20are%20heartened.%20Their%20worst%20fears%20that%20bubbled%20to%20the%20surface%20when%20the%20secretary-general%E2%80%99s%20visit%20was%20hurriedly%20announced%20were%20not%20borne%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20required%20now%20is%20to%20keep%20watch%20for%20%E2%80%98spoilers%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20peace%20process%2C%20and%20they%20include%20many%20influential%20Nepalis%20who%20have%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20developed%20political%20and%20interpersonal%20relationships%20with%20the%20perpetrators%20of%20the%20conflict%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20there%20is%20a%20Western%20diplomat%20(or%20two)%20who%20seems%20to%20have%20a%20low%20opinion%20of%20the%20Nepali%20yearnings%20for%20a%20just%20peace%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20peace%20of%20the%20cemetery.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20civil%20society%20actors%20cautioned%20the%20secretary-general%20in%20a%20letter%20delivered%20as%20he%20departed%20Kathmandu%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20national%20and%20international%20%E2%80%98spoilers%E2%80%99%20wanting%20to%20foist%20a%20perpetrator-friendly%20ending%20to%20the%20peace%20process%20in%20the%20name%20of%20elapsed%20time%20and%20geopolitical%20expediency.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fkanak-mani-dixit%5C%22%3EKanak%20Mani%20Dixit%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20served%20as%20a%20staffer%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%20Secretariat%20in%20New%20York%20from%201982%20to%201990.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipsnews.net%2F2023%2F11%2Fantonio-guterres-nepal-transitional-justice-fore%2F%5C%22%3Estory%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ipsnews.net%2F%5C%22%3EIPS%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699014610000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03153658%2FF9m-3Tka4AAyqdf.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fantonio-guterres-in-nepal-transitional-justice-to-the-fore%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20UN%20secretary-general%20clearly%20understands%20that%2C%20worldwide%2C%20the%20fraught%20arena%20of%20transitional%20justice%20has%20had%20too%20few%20successes.%20Herein%20lies%20the%20importance%20of%20Nepal%2C%20where%20the%20process%20is%20stuck%20but%20the%20victims%20and%20rights%20defenders%20have%20not%20let%20go.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fantonio-guterres-in-nepal-transitional-justice-to-the-fore%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98One%20Child%20Is%20Killed%20Every%2010%20Minutes%20in%20Gaza%2C%E2%80%99%20Says%20Save%20the%20Children%20Country%20Director%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03163854%2FKR-2-Nov-B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20week%2C%20one%20child%20has%20been%20killed%20every%2010%20minutes%20in%20Gaza.%20Last%20week%2C%20it%20was%20one%20child%20every%2015%20minutes.%20I%20dread%20to%20think%20what%20will%20be%20the%20situation%20next%20week%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Jason%20Lee%2C%20Save%20the%20Children%E2%80%99s%20country%20director%20for%20the%20Occupied%20Palestinian%20Territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2025-minute%20interview%20with%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Lee%2C%20who%20was%20speaking%20from%20East%20Jerusalem%2C%20said%20that%20in%20the%20last%2028%20days%2C%20more%20children%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20than%20in%20all%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20conflicts%20since%202019.%20There%20can%20be%20no%20more%20horrifying%20indication%20of%20the%20enormity%20of%20the%20plight%20facing%20the%20children%20of%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20asked%20about%20the%20accuracy%20and%20reliability%20of%20the%20death%20toll%20figures%2C%20particularly%20because%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F26%2Fappalling-why-has-biden-cast-doubt-on-the-palestinian-death-count%5C%22%3Ehas%20cast%20doubt%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20overall%20death%20count.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Philippe%20Lazzarini%20of%20the%20UNRWA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F27%2Fun-says-gaza-health-ministry-death-tolls-in-previous-wars%5C%22%3Ehas%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20death%20count%20is%20reliably%20accurate%2C%20Lee%20gave%20several%20reasons%20for%20accepting%20the%20death%20count%20put%20out%20by%20the%20Hamas%20Ministry%20of%20Health%20in%20Gaza.%20It%20aligns%20with%20the%20death%20counts%20from%20earlier%20Hamas-Israel%20wars%2C%20although%2C%20in%20overall%20terms%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20much%20greater%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELee%20gave%20graphic%20details%20of%20the%20conditions%20in%20hospitals%2C%20how%20long%20they%20can%20function%2C%20and%20what%20will%20happen%20when%20they%20completely%20run%20out%20of%20standby%20fuel%20and%20generators.%20He%20said%20that%20could%20happen%20in%2048%20hours.%20That%20means%20many%20of%20the%20patients%20in%20those%20hospitals%20%E2%80%93%20and%20particularly%20young%20children%20%E2%80%93%20will%20face%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20slow%20painful%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20spoke%20about%20the%20situation%20that%20children%20are%20facing%2C%20especially%20those%20who%20have%20not%20been%20injured.%20He%20talks%20about%20the%20drastic%20shortage%20of%20clean%20water%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20children%20are%20now%20relying%20on%20brackish%20water%20or%20saline%20water%20from%20old%2C%20disused%20wells.%20The%20threat%20of%20a%20public%20health%20catastrophe%20is%20looming%20and%20getting%20closer%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20discussed%20the%20cumulative%20impact%20on%20children%E2%80%99s%20well-being%20and%20mental%20state%2C%20resulting%20from%20living%20under%20an%20Israeli%20blockade%20in%20Gaza%20since%202007-2008%2C%20which%20amounts%20to%2016%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F0Pe2n0V0fzE%3Fsi%3DUpLR1uceeWBo-8mu%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699012818000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03163854%2FKR-2-Nov-B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fone-child-is-killed-every-10-minutes-in-gaza-says-save-the-children-country-director%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jason%20Lee%20told%20Karan%20Thapar%20that%20in%20the%20last%2028%20days%2C%20more%20children%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Gaza%20than%20in%20all%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20conflicts%20sin